To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All records and documents related to high-profile CIA operations from 1950 to 2000, including but not limited to covert actions, espionage, and counterintelligence activities. Please provide any available information on the objectives, strategies, and outcomes of these operations.

If any redactions are necessary, I ask that you justify them under the specific exemptions of the FOIA.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Gabriel Garcia

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All signals intelligence (SIGINT) reports and documents pertaining to major international events and crises from 1950 to 2000. This includes, but is not limited to, the Cuban Missile Crisis, the Vietnam War, and the Iranian Revolution. Please provide any available information on the intercepted communications, analysis, and impact of this intelligence on U.S. policy and decision-making.

 If any redactions are necessary, I ask that you justify them under the specific exemptions of the FOIA.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Gabriel Garcia
